.Im MicroEmacs shell
.so me.tni
.TH gdb 3
.XI gdb - "GNU Debugger"
.XI dbx - "UNIX Debugger"
.SH NAME
.Me "|gdb"
gdb \- GNU Debugger
.br
.Me "|dbx"
dbx \- UNIX Debugger
.Me $a
.SH SYNOPSIS
.na
.B gdb
"\fIprogram-name\fR"
"\fIadditional-args\fR"
.br
.B dbx
"\fIprogram-name\fR"
"\fIadditional-args\fR"
.ad
.SH DESCRIPTION
\fBgdb\fR  and  \fBdbx\fR  provide an editor  interface  to the GNU and native
system debuggers,  respectively. On running either command then an interactive
shell  window is opened to the  debugger  command line  interface.  \*(mS then
interprets  the  information  from the debugger  interface and opens files and
hilights the current line as required.  The current line is  maintained  while
single stepping through the code.
.PP
Buffers opened and referenced by the debugger have the key \fCF9\fR  bound to
setting a break point.
.SH NOTES
\fBgdb\fR and \fBdbx\fR are macros defined in file \fChkipipe.emf\fR.
